derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English: from late Latin obfuscat- 'darkened', from the verb obfuscare, based on Latin fuscus 'dark'

entry.def: To obfuscate something means to deliberately make it seem confusing and difficult to understand.

example.ex: They are obfuscating the issue, as only insurance companies can...
